Chinese Envoy Attends Former Sri Lankan PM's Funeral 
A Chinese special envoy attended the state funeral held Saturday for
Sri Lanka's late woman Prime Minister Sirimavo Bandaranaike, who passed
away on election day Tuesday, at her ancestral home in Horagolla, 40
kilometers northeast of here.
He Luli, vice chairman of the Chinese National People's Congress
Standing Committee, was among high-level officials from a number of
countries at the funeral, accompanied by Chinese Ambassador to Sri
Lanka Jiang Qinzheng.
The special envoy and her 11-member entourage arrived here on Friday
evening.
